     This is a brief description of the Mobile Communications
Channel Simulator originally developed by the MITRE Corporation and
modified by the MIT Lincoln Laboratory.  The simulator is described in
MITRE Working Paper WN 94B0000003 "First Quarterly Progress Report:
Generic Channel Simulator" by Phillip A. Bello, Christopher A. Nissen,
Jeffrey J. Blanchard, and Robert C. Boice, 28 April, 1994 and in MITRE
Project Report 8632L "Generic Channel Simulator" by Phillip A. Bello,
Christopher A. Nissen, and Jeffrey J. Blanchard.

